    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter" xml:id="letter_1673_03_29_mm2lc_raw" n="28" facs="DSCF8519">
                <head type="raw" xml:lang="it" />
                <note resp="#smn" xml:id="archive-note">
                Collocazione II-C.P.1. lettera 28
                Lettere di Maria Mancini – 1673
                Numero d'ordine – 11 

                D. Maria Colonna-Mancini –

                =

                Lettera al Contestabile Colonna
                in data	29 Marzo 1673 da Torino
                Sigillo – tutta di pugno –

                oggetto:
                </note>
                <pb facs="DSCF8520"/>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[On the left side of the image, the rectangularly folded paper with address written on outside: 
                "A Monsieur
                Monsieur le Conestable 
                Colonna
                A Rome"
                + 2 red wax seals]]
                </note>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[On the left side of the image, just to the left of the center fold, parallel with the fold, is written the date by an archivist or a secretary. The ink looks slightly different from Marie's ink.]]    
                </note>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[On the right half of the sheet:]]   
                </note>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName key="turin">De thurin</placeName>
                        <date when="1673-03-29">ce 29<hi rend="sup">me</hi> mars 1673</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Son debitrice a due vostre ma come sono stata un poco indispota non potei pontualmente risponder ricevo la poliza di cambio di cento novanta doppie; et vi ringratio di quanto avete operato per facilitarmi il modo di riscoterli; in quanto a pietro marchese nol limpieguero piu a niente; et lo conosco meglio di voi; credo ch se nandera presto a ritrovar mio fratello non essendomi quy necessario; godo ch' li miei ragazzi stiano tutti bene abracciateli per me et dateli la beneditione in mio nome et al solito mi sottoscrivo vostra</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute></salute>
                    <signed><persName key="mancini-marie">M. M. C.</persName></signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <div type="letter" xml:id="letter_1673_03_29_mm2lc_edit" n="28" facs="DSCF8519">
                <head type="edit" xml:lang="it" />
                <pb facs="DSCF8520"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName key="turin">De Turin</placeName> 
                        <date when="1673-03-29">ce 29<hi rend="sup">me</hi> mars <ref type="annotate" xml:id="a1673_03_29_mm2lc" n="1" style="Note that Marie’s Italian is influenced by her French, and she often writes the dates of her Italian letters in French.">1673</ref></date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Son debitrice di due <ref type="annotate" xml:id="b1673_03_29_mm2lc" n="2" style="The meaning is 'due vostre lettere.'">vostre</ref> ma come sono stata un poco indisposta non potei puntualmente rispondere; ricevo la polizza di cambio di centonovanta doppie; e vi ringrazio di quanto avete operato per facilitarmi il modo di riscuoterli. In quanto a Pietro Marchese, non lo impiegher&#242; pi&#249; a niente, e lo conosco meglio di voi; credo che se ne andr&#224; presto a trovar mio fratello, non essendomi qui necessario. Godo che i miei ragazzi stiano tutti bene, abbracciateli per me e dategli la benedizione in mio nome ed al solito mi sottoscrivo vostra</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute></salute>
                    <signed><persName key="mancini-marie">M. M. C.</persName></signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <div type="letter" xml:id="letter_1673_03_29_mm2lc_translation" n="28" facs="DSCF8519">
                <head type="translation" xml:lang="en" />
                <pb facs="DSCF8520"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName key="turin">Turin</placeName>, 
                        <date when="1673-03-29">29 March 1673</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am in your debt for two letters, but as I have been a bit indisposed, I was not able to reply punctually. I am in receipt of the bill of exchange for one hundred ninety doppie, and I thank you for what you have done to facilitate my cashing it in. Regarding Pietro Marchese, I will no longer employ him for anything, and I know him better than you; I believe he will soon go to join my brother, since he’s of no use to me here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am glad that my boys are all well; hug them for me and give them my blessing, and as always, I sign off as your</salute>
                    <signed><persName key="mancini-marie">M. M. C.</persName></signed>
            </div>
